SIMPLE: caloric
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Caloric
<hw>Ca*lor"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>calor</ets>
heat; cf. F. <ets>calorique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>The
principle of heat, or the agent to which the phenomena of heat and
combustion were formerly ascribed; -- not now used in scientific
nomenclature, but sometimes used as a general term for heat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Caloric</qex> expands all bodies.</q>
<rj><qau>Henry.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caloric</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Caloric
<hw>Ca*lor"ic</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
caloric.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Caloric engine</b></col>, <cd>a kind of engine operated
by heated air.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caloricity</ent>⟦br⟧
